{"type":"message","id":"80bbbbd5","parentId":"4867e457","timestamp":"2026-05-13T10:58:55.144Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is seeing these errors after the gateway restart. Let me analyze them:\n\n1. **`marked interrupted main session failed: agent:main:main (transcript tail is not resumable)`** - This is normal after a restart. When the gateway restarts, it tries to recover the main session, but since the transcript can't be resumed, it marks it as failed. This is expected behavior - the old session is dead, a new one was created when I replied earlier.\n\n2. **`main-session restart recovery complete: recovered=0 failed=1 skipped=0`** - Same thing, just the summary. Recovered 0 sessions, failed 1 (the old main session). This is normal after restart.\n\n3. **`liveness warning: event_loop_delay` with max 9454ms** - This is the event loop delay again, happening during startup. The model-prewarm (2298ms) and session-locks (1111ms) are blocking the event loop during startup. After the initial startup phase this goes away.\n\nLet me check the current state to see if things are stable now.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Gateway 刚重启完，这些是启动期的残留正常行为。我检查一下现在是不是已经稳定了。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_qvsnds9y9aYJnegvJpBh7057","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw status 2>&1","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":1359,"output":324,"cacheRead":33792,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":35475,"cost":{"input":0.00019026,"output":0.00009072000000000001,"cacheRead":0.000946176,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.001227156}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778669931765,"responseId":"781559c2-5de2-4492-856d-84477ce040a9"}}
