{"type":"message","id":"569668aa","parentId":"a2ef9d7e","timestamp":"2026-05-13T11:52:52.542Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is showing me an error: `spawn UNKNOWN` when trying to run a Unity build pipeline command. The `spawn UNKNOWN` error in Node.js on Windows typically means the executable path is wrong or there's an issue with how the process is being spawned.\n\nLet me analyze the command:\n- It's trying to run Unity.exe from `C:\\Program Files\\Unity\\Hub\\Editor\\2020.3.49f1\\Editor\\Unity.exe`\n- The project is at `E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv`\n- It's using PowerShell's `Start-Process`\n\nThe `spawn UNKNOWN` error on Windows is often caused by:\n1. The executable not existing at the specified path\n2. Path containing spaces without proper quoting\n3. The executable path has some issue\n\nLet me check if Unity exists at that path first.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"来看看 `spawn UNKNOWN` 是什么原因。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_Qf1sCEuetbkuu2hmA5L26492","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Test-Path \"C:\\Program Files\\Unity\\Hub\\Editor\\2020.3.49f1\\Editor\\Unity.exe\"","timeout":5}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_01_bLMxru7wiQDJN0EXlt0B4789","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem \"C:\\Program Files\\Unity\\Hub\\Editor\" -Directory 2>&1","timeout":5}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":4555,"output":351,"cacheRead":35072,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":39978,"cost":{"input":0.0006377,"output":0.00009828,"cacheRead":0.000982016,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.001717996}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778673168640,"responseId":"0538fe23-aca0-4d62-843b-9613c3236e5f"}}
