{"type":"message","id":"c59f4327","parentId":"48adc0bc","timestamp":"2026-05-13T11:53:20.154Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Hmm, no output. Unity.exe with `--version` may output to stderr. Let me try a different approach.\n\nThe main issue is the `spawn UNKNOWN` error. Looking at the error message more carefully:\n\n```\nspawn failed: runId=lucky-cedar reason=Error: spawn UNKNOWN\n[tools] exec failed: spawn UNKNOWN raw_params={\"command\":\"...\",\"timeout\":30}\n```\n\nThis was from a sub-agent (`runId=lucky-cedar`). The `spawn UNKNOWN` is a Node.js error that occurs when `child_process.spawn()` fails on Windows with an unknown system error.\n\nCommon causes on Windows:\n1. **Path too long** - Windows has a 260 character path limit for some APIs\n2. **File in use** - The executable or a DLL it needs is locked\n3. **Antivirus blocking** - Some AV software blocks process creation\n4. **Windows Error 0 (ERROR_SUCCESS but failed)** - This is what spawn UNKNOWN usually maps to\n\nLooking at the raw command - it's a multi-line PowerShell script being passed as `-Command`. The issue is likely that the `timeout: 30` (30 seconds) was not enough, and when exec tried to spawn it, something went wrong.\n\nActually, wait - the error says \"spawn UNKNOWN\" which means it failed at the spawn level, not during execution. This could mean:\n1. The command string is somehow malformed when passed to PowerShell\n2. There's an issue with how exec was called from the sub-agent\n\nLet me look at the sub-agent sessions to see which one had the issue.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_SJhjGCTlcxThTpBaAncf2534","name":"sessions_list","arguments":{"kinds":["direct"],"includeLastMessage":true,"search":"lucky-cedar"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":36,"output":433,"cacheRead":40960,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":41429,"cost":{"input":0.00000504,"outpu