{"type":"message","id":"4b3e28b1","parentId":"98100b33","timestamp":"2026-05-13T11:53:26.434Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The session with that run ID is already gone. Let me check recent sessions.\n\nLet me look at this from a different angle. The `spawn UNKNOWN` error happened. Let me try to reproduce it by running the same command format that was used. The command was:\n\n```powershell\n$unityPath = \"C:\\Program Files\\Unity\\Hub\\Editor\\2020.3.49f1\\Editor\\Unity.exe\"\n$projectPath = \"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\"\n$logFile = \"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log\"\n$method = \"YYZY.BuildPipeline.BuildPipeline.RunHotUpdatePipeline\"\n\n$p = Start-Process -FilePath $unityPath -ArgumentList \"-batchmode\",\"-projectPath\",\"`\"$projectPath`\"\",\"-executeMethod\",\"$method\",\"-logFile\",\"`\"$logFile`\"\",\"-quit\" -NoNewWindow -PassThru\nWrite-Host \"UNITY_PID=$($p.Id)\"\n```\n\nThis was being passed as a raw command with `timeout: 30`. The `spawn UNKNOWN` might be because:\n1. The command is too long for a single `powershell -Command` string\n2. The quoting of `$projectPath` using backtick quotes `` `\"$projectPath`\" `` might cause issues\n\nActually I think the real issue is that the sub-agent was trying to run this directly via exec, and the `exec` tool from TOOLS.md describes this as a sub-agent task. The issue might be that the sub-agent called exec with a command that was multi-line and had special characters that didn't parse correctly.\n\nLet me just check if the bat file works properly.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_fCczFgYJ4S92NBNJ8zXS6177","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"type \"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\RunBuildPipelineHotUpdate.bat\" 2>&1","timeout":5}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":111,"output":470,"cacheRead":41344,"cach